# Web UI/UX Agent Scope

## Allowed

- `frontend/src/views/` — React components (UI only)
- `frontend/src/controllers/` — hooks (`useOutfitController`, etc.)
- `frontend/src/services/ApiService.ts` — only when spec requires API client changes
- `frontend/src/models/` — only when spec requires DTO changes
- `frontend/src/utils/` — shared helpers (prompt, progress steps, preferences)
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` — route shell (`react-router-dom`)
- `frontend/src/navigation/routes.ts` — path constants

## Forbidden

- `ios-client/**` — iOS agent owns this
- `backend/**` — orchestrator or backend step owns this

## Architecture

Views → Controllers (hooks) → Services → Models. Keep views thin; put orchestration in controllers.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS; brand tokens: `brand-blue`, glass/slate cards
- Match iOS visual intent via gradient `#4facfe` → `#c471ed` and dark slate backgrounds
- Reference: `WEB_USER_INTERACTION.md` for state and flow patterns

## Platform-specific (keep on web)

- `localStorage` for JWT (`auth_token`) and preferences
- React Router (`BrowserRouter`, shareable URLs)
- Drag/drop and web file inputs for images

## Parity

Behavior and copy must match the active spec and iOS implementation. Sync contract files with iOS when models, API calls, or progress steps change.

## Tests (Twin UI — required)

- Unit: `*.test.tsx` / `*.test.ts` colocated or under `src/`
- Integration: `*.integration.test.tsx`; use `renderApp()` from `src/test/renderWithRouter.tsx`
- MSW: update `src/test/msw/handlers.ts` when API changes
- Run: `npm test -- --watchAll=false` before returning
- Assert new behavior from spec — not smoke-only tests
